VL  - 14
IS  - 2
SP  - 241
EP  - 250
PY  - 1984
DA  - 1984/09/01/
SN  - 0304-3932
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3932(84)90062-X
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030439328490062X
AB  - In this paper the model of the transactions demand for money of Baumol (1952) is extended to an economy where transactions are conducted in two currencies. The currency substitution hypothesis - that the domestic demand for domestic money depends on the expected rate of depreciation, as well as the domestic rate of interest and level of income - is derived from the model. In addition, several new insights into the implications of currency substitution are provided.
ER  - 
